OL,3,CAmbulance critical incident stood down
OL,4,Cbut 'significant' pressure remains
OL,6,FJudith Bryce, the Trust's Assistant
OL,7,FDirector of Operations, said: "We
OL,8,Fwould once again like to apologise to
OL,9,Fall those patients who have waited far
OL,10,Ftoo long for an ambulance during an
OL,11,Fextremely challenging 48-hour period.
OL,13,F"Please only call 999 in a life-
OL,14,Fthreatening emergency, and if it's not
OL,15,Fa life-threatening emergency, please
OL,16,Fconsider one of the many alternatives
OL,17,Fto 999, starting with the NHS 111
OL,18,FWales symptom checkers as well as your
OL,19,Flocal pharmacist, Minor Injuries Unit
OL,20,Fand GP."
